{"first_name":"Robert","last_name":"May","permalink":"robert-may","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/robert-may","homepage_url":"","birthplace":"","twitter_username":"","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"Mohr Davidow Ventures","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"","alias_list":"","created_at":"Mon Jun 02 19:38:31 UTC 2008","updated_at":"Wed Jun 01 19:19:28 UTC 2011","overview":"<p>Robert is the Chief Operating Officer and Chief Financial Officer for Founders Fund in San Francisco, CA.</p>\n\n<p>Prior to joining Founders Fund, Robert spent four years as the Chief Financial Officer at Thomas Weisel Venture Partners, an early-stage technology venture investment firm.  Prior to joining TWVP, Robert was the Controller at Mohr, Davidow Ventures, an early-stage venture firm with $1.2 billion under management. He was responsible for fund financing, reporting, portfolio and Limited Partner management. Prior to Mohr Davidow, Robert was a Financial Analyst for Hewlett-Packard in the Integrated Circuit Business Division, specializing in the Semiconductor industry. While at HP, he helped structure an LOA between three major chip manufacturers to research Fe-RAM development and manufacturing. Prior to HP, Robert spent seven years in operations as a Production Control Analyst for former optical data storage manufacturer Drexler Technologies. </p>\n\n<p>Robert graduated Magna Cum Laude from San Jose State University with a BS in Business Administration, emphasis in Finance. He was an original member of the Board of Directors for the Private Equity CFO Association (PECFOA), an agency comprised of senior executive finance professionals. </p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,99],"assets/images/resized/0001/9824/19824v5-max-150x150.jpg"],[[250,166],"assets/images/resized/0001/9824/19824v5-max-250x250.jpg"],[[450,299],"assets/images/resized/0001/9824/19824v5-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":"<p>www.foundersfund.com</p>"},"de